The paper deals with scheduling moldable tasks on parallel systems, which is a problem in distributed computing (cs.DC) and scheduling algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses optimizing scheduling objectives, which falls under control systems (cs.SY) and optimization (cs.PF). Finally, the paper proposes approximation algorithms, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
